  41,13,"If they turn away, then say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúI warn you of a ňĻmightyňļ blast, like the one that befell ‚Äô»ād and Tham√Ľd.‚ÄĚ"
  41,14,"The messengers had come to them from all angles, ňĻproclaiming,ňļ ‚ÄúWorship none but God.‚ÄĚ They responded, ‚ÄúHad our Lord willed, He could have easily sent down angels ňĻinsteadňļ. So we totally reject what you have been sent with.‚ÄĚ"
  41,15,"As for ‚Äô»ād, they acted arrogantly throughout the land with no right, boasting, ‚ÄúWho is superior to us in might?‚ÄĚ Did they not see that God ňĻHimselfňļ, Who created them, was far superior to them in might? Still they persisted in denying Our signs"
