  41,21,"They will ask their skin ňĻfuriouslyňļ, ‚ÄúWhy have you testified against us?‚ÄĚ It will say, ‚ÄúWe have been made to speak by God, Who causes all things to speak. He ňĻis the One Whoňļ created you the first time, and to Him you were bound to return"
  41,22,"You did not ňĻbother toňļ hide yourselves from your ears, eyes, and skin to prevent them from testifying against you. Rather, you assumed that God did not know much of what you used to do"
